<DESC><![CDATA[[b]The Security Council,[/b]

[b]Declaring[/b] that this august body&#39;s authority lies through declarations, whether it a commendation or condemnation, a liberation or injunction, or simply a straightforward declaration,

[b]Explaining[/b] that before, nations across the multiverse have time and time again proposed proposals that this Council has put onto the books, that&#39;ve recognized matters unpertaining to a singular country or region (or really any nations, for that matter),

[b]Calling back[/b] in said time to instances of the above clause when this assembly has enjoyed declarations of silly and satirical nature,

[b]Lambasting[/b] the stagnation this body faces when the world is lowering its volume and querulous debates; when most of the commendable already has been given their honors and salutes, the majority of the condemnable long been shamed and verbally defenestrated,

[b]Accepting[/b] the ability of nations to assign their most advanced or amateur authors to the Security Council to accumulate articles of creative addresses,

[b]Resorting[/b] to rejection when a piece of penning is ultimately unacceptable, not of malevolent malfeasance, but of benevolent beholding,

[b]Endorsing[/b] this assembly&#39;s ability to deny a declaration such as this declaration when it is witnessed to be undoubtedly weak and unenjoyable, and clearly crafted with breaching boredom originating from a nation&#39;s nests,

[b]Hereby declares the Security Council&#39;s somewhat positive declaration on the declarations of declarations.[/b]]]></DESC>
